(NAN)The vice Presidential Candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Mr Peter Obi has urged President Muhammadu Buhari and the 29 state governors sworn-in on Wednesday to increase tempo of development in Nigeria. He appealed to the president and governors to use the event to reflect about the country, about the life of service and about the condition of Nigeria. Obi said that upon reflection, he was sure they would realise that they had a lot of work to do in different aspects.